<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb610fa0b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300b–16"><num value="300b–16">§ 300b–16.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations for newborn screening programs and activities</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb610fa0c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300b–16/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to carry out sections 300b–8, 300b–9, 300b–10, and 300b–11 of this title, $11,900,000 for each of fiscal years 2015 through 2019; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idb610fa0d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s300b–16/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to carry out <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s300b–12">section 300b–12 of this title</ref>, $8,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2015 through 2019.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idb610fa0e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1944-07-01/ch373">July 1, 1944, ch. 373</ref>, title XI, § 1117, as added <ref href="/us/pl/113/240/s10">Pub. L. 113–240, § 10</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2856">128 Stat. 2856</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
